## Why This Is Asked

Tests DP with partitioning and a gap constraint, requiring prefix sums, 2D DP, and backtracking to output block endpoints. Encourages thinking about edge cases when n is large and k near n/gap.

## Key Concepts

- DP over prefixes with fixed block counts
- Enforcing gap constraints between blocks
- Backtracking to recover endpoints
- Time: O(nk); Space: O(nk)

## Code Example

```javascript
function maxKBlocks(profits, k, g) {
  const n = profits.length
  const S = Array(n + 1).fill(0)
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) S[i + 1] = S[i] + profits[i]
  const dp = Array.from({ length: n + 1 }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-Infinity))
  const take = Array.from({ length: n + 1 }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-1))
  dp[0][0] = 0
  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (let t = 0; t <= k; t++) dp[i][t] = Math.max(dp[i][t], dp[i - 1][t])
    for (let t = 1; t <= k; t++) {
      for (let l = 0; l <= i - 1 - g; l++) {
        const val = dp[l][t - 1] + (S[i] - S[l])
        if (val > dp[i][t]) { dp[i][t] = val; take[i][t] = l }
      }
    }
  }
  const blocks = []
  let i = n, t = k
  while (t > 0) {
    const l = take[i][t]
    blocks.unshift([l, i - 1])
    i = l
    t--
  }
  return { value: dp[n][k], blocks }
}
```

