## Key Concepts

- Palindrome table isPal[i][j] for substring s[i..j]
- dist[i][j] stores number of distinct characters in s[i..j]
- DP state dp[i][t]: best score for first i chars partitioned into t palindromes
- Transition: for all j < i with isPal[j][i-1], dp[i][t] = max(dp[i][t], dp[j][t-1] + dist[j][i-1])
- Reconstruction via parent pointers to recover cut positions
- Time/space: O(n^2 k) time and O(n^2 k) space

## Code Example

