questions.answer:
Define `dp[i][j][t]` as the maximum value obtainable using the first `i` elements of `A` and the first `j` elements of `B` to form exactly `t` pairs. The transitions are:

- **Skip `A[i]`**: `dp[i-1][j][t]`
- **Skip `B[j]`**: `dp[i][j-1][t]`
- **Form pair `(i, j)`**: `dp[i-1][j-1][t-1] + A[i] * B[j]`, when `t > 0`

**Base cases**: Initialize `dp[0][j][0] = dp[i][0][0] = 0` for all valid `i, j`. All other states default to `-∞`.

**Reconstruction**: Backtrack from `dp[n][m][k]`. When the current state matches the "form pair" transition, record `(i, j)` and move to `dp[i-1][j-1][t-1]`.

**JavaScript Implementation**:
```javascript
function maxWeightTwoSeq(A, B, k) {
  const n = A.length, m = B.length;
  const NEG = -Infinity;
  let dp = Array.from({ length: n + 1 }, () =>
    Array.from({ length: m + 1 }, () => new Array(k + 1).fill(NEG))
  );
  for (let i = 0; i <= n; i++) dp[i][0][0] = 0;
  for (let j = 0; j <= m; j++) dp[0][j][0] = 0;

  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (let j = 1; j <= m; j++) {
      for (let t = 0; t <= k; t++) {
        dp[i][j][t] = Math.max(dp[i-1][j][t], dp[i][j-1][t]);
        if (t > 0) {
          dp[i][j][t] = Math.max(dp[i][j][t], dp[i-1][j-1][t-1] + A[i-1] * B[j-1]);
        }
      }
    }
  }

  const pairs = [];
  let i = n, j = m, t = k;
  while (i > 0 && j > 0 && t > 0) {
    if (dp[i][j][t] === dp[i-1][j-1][t-1] + A[i-1] * B[j-1]) {
      pairs.push([i-1, j-1]);
      i--; j--; t--;
    } else if (dp[i][j][t] === dp[i-1][j][t]) {
      i--;
    } else {
      j--;
    }
  }
  pairs.reverse();
  return { value: dp[n][m][k], pairs };
}
```

