- How would you optimize space to O(nmK) memory or better, and what would be the trade-offs for reconstruction?

## Why This Problem Is Asked
This problem combines prefix DP with an inner backward sweep to compute the optimal segment ending at each position. It tests understanding of state decomposition, reconstruction logic, and handles edge cases like negative values naturally.

## Key Concepts
- DP state: dp[i][t] tracks the optimal value using the first i elements with t segments
- Inner loop: expanding the left boundary computes segment maximum on the fly
- Reconstruction: store predecessor pointers to recover exact subarray boundaries
- Complexity: O(n²k) time, O(nk) space

## Code Example
```javascript
function maxValueSubarrays(A, k) {
    const n = A.length;
    const dp = Array(n + 1).fill(null).map(() => Array(k + 1).fill(-Infinity));
    const prev = Array(n + 1).fill(null).map(() => Array(k + 1).fill(0));
    dp[0][0] = 0;

    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for (let t = 1; t <= k; t++) {
            let curMax = -Infinity;
            for (let l = i; l >= 1; l--) {
                curMax = Math.max(curMax, A[l - 1]);
                const val = (dp[l - 1][t - 1] !== -Infinity ? dp[l - 1][t - 1] + curMax : -Infinity);
                if (val > dp[i][t]) {
                    dp[i][t] = val;
                    prev[i][t] = l;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    const result = [];
    let i = n, t = k;
    while (t > 0 && i > 0) {
        const l = prev[i][t];
        result.unshift([l, i]);
        i = l - 1;
        t--;
    }
    return { value: dp[n][k], boundaries: result };
}
```

## Why This Question Is Asked
This problem assesses your ability to handle non-trivial path constraints in dynamic programming, specifically exact turn counting. It also requires path reconstruction, reflecting real-world interview complexity where identifying a solution isn't sufficient—you must also provide the actual path.

## Key Concepts
- **4D DP state** capturing both position and path history: `(i, j, t, dir)` tracks where you are, how many turns you've made, and your incoming direction
- **Turn counting** via conditional transitions: staying in the same direction doesn't increment the turn count, while switching does
- **Backpointer-based reconstruction** stores the predecessor for each state, enabling full path recovery

## Code Example
```javascript
function maxPathWithKTurns(grid, k) {
  const n = grid.length, m = grid[0].length;
  const dp = Array.from({length: n}, () =>
    Array.from({length: m}, () =>
      Array.from({length: k + 1}, () => [-Infinity, -Infinity])
    )
  );
  dp[0][0][0][0] = dp[0][0][0][1] = grid[0][0];

  const parent = Array.from({length: n}, () =>
    Array.from({length: m}, () =>
      Array.from({length: k + 1}, () => [null, null])
    )
  );

  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    for (let j = 0; j < m; j++) {
      for (let t = 0; t <= k; t++) {
        if (i === 0 && j === 0) continue;
        if (j > 0) {
          const fromRight = dp[i][j-1][t][0];
          const fromDown = t > 0 ? dp[i][j-1][t-1][1] : -Infinity;
          if (fromRight >= fromDown) {
            dp[i][j][t][0] = fromRight + grid[i][j];
            parent[i][j][t][0] = [i, j-1, t, 0];
          } else {
            dp[i][j][t][0] = fromDown + grid[i][j];
            parent[i][j][t][0] = [i, j-1, t-1, 1];
          }
        }
        if (i > 0) {
          const fromDown = dp[i-1][j][t][1];
          const fromRight = t > 0 ? dp[i-1][j][t-1][0] : -Infinity;
          if (fromDown >= fromRight) {
            dp[i][j][t][1] = fromDown + grid[i][j];
            parent[i][j][t][1] = [i-1, j, t, 1];
          } else {
            dp[i][j][t][1] = fromRight + grid[i][j];
            parent[i][j][t][1] = [i-1, j, t-1, 0];
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  const endDir = dp[n-1][m-1][k][0] >= dp[n-1][m-1][k][1] ? 0 : 1;
  const maxSum = dp[n-1][m-1][k][endDir];
  const path = [];
  let cur = [n-1, m-1, k, endDir];

  while (cur) {
    path.unshift([cur[0], cur[1]]);
    cur = parent[cur[0]][cur[1]][cur[2]][cur[3]];
  }

  return { sum: maxSum, path };
}
```

