## Why This Is Asked
Tests DP with partitioning and a nontrivial per-substring cost, plus backtracking to recover partitions.

## Key Concepts
- DP over partitions: dp[i][t]
- Precompute cost[l][r] in O(n^2) via two-pointer mismatches
- Backpointers for reconstruction
- Complexity: O(n^2 k) time, O(n^2) space

## Code Example
```javascript
function minCostPalindromePartitions(s, k) {
  const n = s.length;
  const cost = Array.from({length: n}, ()=> Array(n).fill(0));
  for (let l = 0; l < n; l++) {
    for (let r = l; r < n; r++) {
      let a = l, b = r, c = 0;
      while (a < b) { if (s[a] !== s[b]) c++; a++; b--; }
      cost[l][r] = c;
    }
  }
  const dp = Array.from({length: n}, () => Array(k + 1).fill(Infinity));
  const parent = Array.from({length: n}, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-1));
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) dp[i][1] = cost[0][i];
  for (let t = 2; t <= k; t++) {
    for (let i = t - 1; i < n; i++) {
      for (let p = t - 2; p < i; p++) {
        const val = dp[p][t - 1] + cost[p + 1][i];
        if (val < dp[i][t]) { dp[i][t] = val; parent[i][t] = p; }
      }
    }
  }
  const splits = [];
  let i = n - 1, t = k;
  while (t >= 1) {
    splits.push(i);
    i = parent[i][t];
    t--;
  }
  splits.reverse();
  return { minCost: dp[n - 1][k], partitions: splits };
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you optimize space for large n or small k?
- How would this adapt if cost used a different per-substring metric?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests budgeted DP on strings and reconstruction. 

## Key Concepts
- dp[i][j][d] encodes a subproblem under a deletion budget; 
- palindrome subsequence logic with matches/skips; 
- reconstruction paths under deletion budget.

## Code Example
```javascript
function maxPalWithDeletions(s, k){
  const n=s.length; 
  const dp=Array.from({length:n},()=>Array.from({length:n},()=>Array(k+1).fill(0)));
  for(let i=0;i<n;i++){ dp[i][i][0]=1; for(let d=1; d<=k; d++) dp[i][i][d]=1; }
  for(let len=2; len<=n; len++){
    for(let i=0; i+len-1<n; i++){
      const j=i+len-1;
      for(let d=0; d<=k; d++){
        if(s[i]===s[j]){
          dp[i][j][d]=Math.max(dp[i+1][j-1][d]+2, (d>0?dp[i+1][j][d-1]:0), (d>0?dp[i][j-1][d-1]:0));
        } else {
          dp[i][j][d]=Math.max(dp[i+1][j][d], dp[i][j-1][d], (d>0?dp[i+1][j-1][d-1]:0));
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return Math.max(...Array.from({length:k+1},(_,d)=>dp[0][n-1][d]));
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
